setts%20Institute%20of%20Technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarvard's%20president%2C%20Claudine%20Gay%2C%20apologized%20afterward%20for%20failing%20to%20more%20strongly%20condemn%20threats%20of%20anti-Semitic%20violence%20on%20her%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20words%20amplify%20distress%20and%20pain%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20you%20could%20feel%20anything%20but%20regret%2C%26quot%3B%20Gay%20later%20told%20the%20Harvard%20Crimson%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMagill%20faced%20even%20more%20scathing%20criticism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPennsylvania's%20Democratic%20governor%20called%20her%20performance%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%20shameful%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20major%20donor%20said%20he%20would%20rescind%20a%20%24100%20million%20donation%20to%20the%20university's%20Wharton%20School%20of%20Business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBok%2C%20who%20helms%20the%20university's%20board%20of%20trustees%20--%20a%20body%20that%20handles%20major%20governance%20issues%20--%20said%20Magill%20made%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20unfortunate%20misstep%26quot%3B%20as%20he%20announced%20her%20departure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20was%20not%20herself%20last%20Tuesday%2C%26quot%3B%20Bok%20said%20in%20the%20statement%20published%20by%20the%20school%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20prepared%20and%20over%20lawyered%20given%20the%20hostile%20forum%20and%20high%20stakes%2C%20she%20provided%20a%20legalistic%20answer%20to%20a%20moral%20question%2C%20and%20that%20was%20wrong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20made%20for%20a%20dreadful%2030-second%20sound%20bite%20in%20what%20was%20more%20than%20five%20hours%20of%20testimony.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20his%20own%20resignation%20was%20%26quot%3Beffective%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Bok's%20note%20to%20the%20campus%2C%20he%20said%20Magill%20would%20stay%20in%20her%20post%20until%20an%20interim%20president%20is%20appointed%20and%20would%20remain%20on%20the%20faculty%20of%20the%20