r%20Row%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20had%20an%20%26quot%3Bexceptionally%20difficult%26quot%3B%20challenge%20along%20the%20northern%20borders%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years%20and%20the%20country%20responded%20to%20it%20very%20resolutely%20and%20has%20been%20maintaining%20the%20kind%20of%20military%20deployment%20necessary%20for%20national%20security%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20said%20on%20Saturday%20on%20the%20lingering%20row%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20in%20an%20address%20at%20the%20FICCI%2C%20while%20explaining%20how%20the%20PM%20Modi%20government%20makes%20choices%20after%20choices%20with%20confidence%20however%20difficult%20and%20tough%20they%20may%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20could%20even%20be%20what%20happens%20at%20our%20border.%20Again%20you%20all%20know%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%20we%20have%20had%20an%20exceptionally%20difficult%20time%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20challenges%20on%20our%20northern%20borders%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20though%20this%20happened%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20Covid%2C%20yet%20we%20responded%20very%20resolutely%2C%20very%20determinedly%2C%20and%20to%20date%20we%20are%20still%20deployed%20in%20whatever%20manner%20is%20necessary%20for%20our%20national%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20troops%20are%20locked%20in%20an%20over%20three-year%20confrontation%20in%20certain%20friction%20points%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%20even%20as%20the%20two%20sides%20completed%20disengagement%20from%20several%20areas%20following%20extensive%20diplomatic%20and%20military%20talks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20also%20explained%20how%20India%2C%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20tried%20to%20create%20global%20awareness%20against%20terrorism%20or%20went%20ahead%20for%20cooperation%20under%20the%20Quad%20framework%20though%20there%20was%20a%20narrative%20that%20it%20could%20make%20somebody%20uncomfortable%2C%20seen%20as%20an%20oblique%20reference%20to%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20somebody%20else%20is%20uncomfortable%2C%20that's%20their%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20we%20have%20to%20do%20what%20we%20have%20to%20do.%20However%20difficult%20and%20tough%20that%20is.%20It%20is%20about%20the%20confidence%20of%20being%20able%20to%20exercise%20choice%20after%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20such%20an%20approach%20will%20%26quot%3Bdefine%20us%20as%20Bharat%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20external%20affairs%20minister%20also%20cited%20how%20India%20confronted%20the%20challenge%20of%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20society%20which%20is%20more%20traumatised%20in%20the%20modern%20era%20than%20us%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20terrorism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20noting%20the%20Modi%20government%20showed%20a%20sense%20of%20resolution%20to%20%26quot%3Bshape%26quot%3B%20the%20global%20agenda%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20specifically%20mentioning%20India's%20continuing%20procurement%20of%20crude%20oil%20from%20Russia%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20asserted%20that%20its%20choices%20on%20energy%20purchases%20were%20driven%20by%20national%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20came%20to%20our%20energy%20purchases%2C%20our%20national%20choices%20and%20national%20interests%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20subservient%20to%20the%20political%20correctness%20of%20other%20countries%20who%20by%20the%20way%20had%20made%20their%20own%20arrangements%20to%20soften%20the%20blow%20for%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20maintained%20its%20purchase%20of%20crude%20oil%20from%20Russia%20notwithstanding%20pressure%20from%20the%20West%20to%20not%20do%20so%20in%20view%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20India%20growth%20story%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said%20there%20is%20no%20question%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bworld%20looks%20at%20us%20as%20an%20exceptionally%20strong%20area%20of%20growth%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20made%20big%20decisions%20but%20we%20are%20clearly%20poised%20to%20make%20many%20more.%20We%20have%20nursed%20big%20ambitions%2C%20we%20have%20implemented%20much%20of%20what%20we%20promised%20but%20again%20there%20is%20still%20a%20lot%20we%20have%20to%20achieve%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20me%20Vikshit%20Bharat%20--%20it%20is%20both%20a%20vision%20to%20achieve%20as%20well%20as%20a%20set%20of%20specific%20goals%20and%20a%20short%20description%20of%20it%20would%20be%20to%20really%20how%20to%20make%20India%20a%20developed%20country%20in%20the%20next%2025%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20external%20affairs%20minister%20described%20the%20last%20five%20years%20as%20%26quot%3Bvery%20traumatic%20for%20the%20world%26quot%3B%20and%20cited%20as%20reasons%20the%20%26quot%3BCovid%20shock%26quot%3B%2C%20developments%20in%20Afghanistan%20following%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20the%20US%20troops%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20the%20ongoing%20violence%20in%20the%20Middle-East%20and%20the%20implications%20of%20the%20competition%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20on%20global%20supply%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20said%20the%20world%20is%20today%20moving%20towards%20greater%20insecurity%20and%20more%20protectionism%2C%20adding%20the%20trading%20rules%20implemented%20globally%20in%20the%20last%20two%20to%20three%20decades%20have%20actually%20raised%20a%20lot%20of%20question%20marks%20about%20their%20effectiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20we%20are%20really%20looking%20at%20what%20happens%20when%20trading%20rules%20are%20gamed%20and%20when%20competition%20has%20been%20unfair%20and%20when%20the%20insecurities%20of%20the%20Covid-era%20have%20caused%20many%2