ithin%20the%20Natural%20History%20Museum%20of%20London's%20collection%2C%20researchers%20stumbled%20upon%20a%20treasure%3A%20a%20407-million-year-old%20fossilized%20fungus%2C%20the%20oldest%20evidence%20of%20a%20disease-causing%20fungus%20ever%20found.%20Named%20Potteromyces%20asteroxylicola%2C%20after%20the%20renowned%20mycologist%20Beatrix%20Potter%2C%20this%20ancient%20microbe%20sheds%20light%20on%20the%20early%20history%20of%20disease%20and%20the%20crucial%20role%20fungi%20played%20in%20shaping%20life%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20titled%20%26quot%3BA%20fungal%20plant%20pathogen%20discovered%20in%20the%20Devonian%20Rhynie%20Chert%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41467-023-43276-1%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENature%20Communications.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20a%20release%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fnews%2F2023-12-fungus-oldest-disease-causing-species-date.html%5C%22%3ENatural%20History%20Museum%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mr%20Beatrix's%20drawings%20and%20study%20of%20the%20growth%20of%20fungi%2C%20which%20were%20in%20some%20cases%20decades%20ahead%20of%20scientific%20research%2C%20have%20garnered%20her%20a%20reputation%20as%20a%20significant%20figure%20in%20mycology.%20Potteromyces%20was%20discovered%20in%20fossil%20samples%20from%20the%20Rhynie%20Chert%2C%20a%20crucial%20geological%20site%20in%20Scotland.%20The%20site%20is%20known%20for%20a%20remarkably%20preserved%20Early%20Devonian%20community%20of%20plants%20and%20animals%2C%20including%20bacteria%20and%20fungi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20study%2C%20completed%20in%20collaboration%20with%20mycologists%20at%20the%20Royal%20Botanic%20Gardens%2C%20Kew%2C%20suggests%20that%20disease-causing%20fungi%2C%20such%20as%20ash%20die-back%20currently%20decimating%20the%20UK's%20native%20ash%20trees%2C%20and%20fungi%20that%20can%20circulate%20nutrients%20that%20plants%20and%20other%20