f-1235829245%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fasia%2Fsingapore-spain-animation-violinist-atf-1235829245%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20Blocked%2036%2C838%20Social%20Media%20Posts%20in%20Past%205%20Years%2C%20X-Corp%20Topped%20the%20Chart%20Among%20Platforms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15203648%2FThe-Wire-10.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EBetween%202018%20and%20October%202023%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20issued%20orders%20to%20take%20down%2036%2C838%20social%20media%20posts.%20The%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20the%20blocked%20URLs%20relates%20to%20X%20(formerly%2C%20Twitter)%2C%20as%20a%20total%20of%2013%2C660%20posts%20were%20taken%20down%2C%20the%20government%20told%20parliament%20on%20Friday%2C%20December%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20information%20was%20disclosed%20by%20the%20government%20in%20response%20to%20questions%20raised%20by%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20John%20Brittas%20of%20the%20CPI%20(M).%20Most%20posts%2FURLs%20(9%2C849)%20were%20taken%20down%20in%202020%2C%20the%20year%20when%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20broke%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%2C%20representing%20Kerala%2C%20sought%20to%20know%20from%20the%20government%20the%20number%20and%20details%20of%20directions%2Forders%20issued%20by%20the%20government%20during%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20under%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%202000%20and%20Rules%20made%20thereunder%2C%20directing%20intermediaries%20and%20digital%20media%20to%20delete%2C%20modify%20or%20block%20any%20content%2C%20information%2C%20data%20or%20communication%20link.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20sought%20information%20year-wise%20and%20organisation-wise%3B%20and%20the%20number%20and%20details%20of%20directions%2Forders%20issued%20by%20the%20government%20during%20the%20last%20five%20years%20directing%20the%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20including%20Twitter%20and%20Facebook%2C%20to%20block%20or%20remove%20posts%2C%20entire%20accounts%2C%20or%20topic%20hashtags.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20the%20government%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20policies%20of%20the%20government%20are%20aimed%20at%20ensuring%20that%20the%20internet%20in%20India%20is%20open%2C%20safe%2C%20trusted%2C%20and%20accountable%20to%20all%20users.%20Accordingly%2C%20the%20government%20issues%20lawful%20directions%20for%20blocking%20access%20to%20information%20by%20the%20public%20under%20Section%2069A%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%20Act%2C%202000%20which%20provides%20power%20to%20the%20government%20to%20issue%20such%20directions%20if%20it%20is%20necessary%20or%20expedient%20to%20do%20so%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%2C%20defence%20of%20India%2C%20security%20of%20the%20state%2C%20friendly%20relations%20with%20foreign%20States%20or%20public%20order%20or%20for%20inciting%20cognisable%20offence%20relating%20to%20above.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20blocked%20posts%20relate%20to%20X%20(13%2C660)%2C%20it%20is%20followed%20by%20Facebook%20(10%2C197)%2C%20YouTube%20(5%2C759)%2C%20Others%20(4%2C199)%2C%20and%20Instagram%20(3%2C023).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fmusk-twitter-takedown-government-compliance%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%2C%20after%20Elon%20Musk%20took%20over%2C%20X%20Corp%20has%20been%20significantly%20more%20compliant%20with%20government%20orders%20for%20censorship%20or%20surveillance%2C%20including%20from%20India%2C%20going%20against%20Musk%E2%80%99s%20promise%20of%20ushering%20in%20a%20new%20era%20of%20free%20speech%20and%20disallowing%20political%20interference%20on%20social%20media.%20For%20instance%2C%20between%20October%2027%2C%202022%2C%20and%20April%2027%2C%202023%2C%20India%20made%2050%20requests%20which%20was%20the%20third-highest%20in%20the%20world.%20Bef